In general, using `performSelector` is discouraged in Objective-C because it can lead to hard-to-debug runtime crashes or leaks, especially if the selector does not exist or takes the wrong arguments. Instead of relying on `performSelector`, consider using a more type-safe alternative, such as block-based APIs or explicit method calls.

