To split a string into substrings of equal size in Java, you can use the substring() method in a loop. Here is an example code snippet to split a string into substrings of equal size:

```
public static String[] splitEqually(String text, int size) {
    // Check the arguments for validity
    if (text == null || size <= 0) {
        return null;
    }

    // Calculate the number of substrings
    int numSubstrings = (int) Math.ceil(((double) text.length()) / ((double) size));

    // Create an array to store the substrings
    String[] result = new String[numSubstrings];

    // Loop through the string, extracting substrings of the specified size
    int start = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < numSubstrings; i++) {
        if (start + size > text.length()) {
            result[i] = text.substring(start);
        } else {
            result[i] = text.substring(start, start + size);
        }
        start += size;
    }

    return result;
}
```

You can call this method by passing the string and the desired size of substrings as arguments:

```
String[] substrings = splitEqually("Hello world", 4);
```

This will return an array containing the substrings {"Hell", "o wo", "rld"}.

