Yes, ADO.NET provides functionality to load a CSV file into a DataTable. You can use the `TextFieldParser` class to parse the CSV file and then fill the DataTable with the parsed data.

Here's an example code snippet to do this:

```csharp
using Microsoft.VisualBasic.FileIO; // Required for TextFieldParser

// Create a DataTable to hold the data
DataTable dataTable = new DataTable();

// Open the CSV file
using (TextFieldParser parser = new TextFieldParser("path/to/csv/file.csv"))
