1. Make sure your ListView adapter implements the Filterable interface.

2. Override the `getFilter()` method in your adapter class and return a filter object that will be used to filter the data.

3. In the `onTextChanged()` method of your textChangeListener, get the filter object from your adapter and use it to filter the data based on the user's input.

4. After filtering the data, call `notifyDataSetChanged()` on your adapter to update the ListView.

