```

Note that this approach requires the code running in your thread to periodically check if the thread has been interrupted, typically by using `Thread.currentThread().isInterrupted()`.

However, you should be careful when interrupting threads, as it may cause unexpected behavior or leave resources in an inconsistent state. It's generally better to design your code to be cooperative with thread interruption and use other mechanisms such as locking and atomic variables to coordinate between threads where possible.

For more information on proper thread management in Java, I recommend reading the official documentation and following best practices outlined in tutorials and blog posts such as [this one](https://www.baeldung.com/java-thread-stop).

